 this time and without measuring cup, mix <b>speed 3<b>, adding eggs one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid, stopping when eggs are fully incorporated. Insert measuring cup and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Transfer mixture to a piping bag fitted with a 1 cm plain nozzle then pipe 18-20 fingers, 3 cm long, on prepared baking trays."},{"content":"Place trays in oven then carefully pour 100 g cold water into roasting tin in bottom of oven. Bake for 20-25 minutes (200°C) or until risen, golden brown and crisp. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl. Remove trays from oven and slice a small slit on the side of each éclair to release steam. Return to oven for 5 minutes (200°C) to dry out then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Creamy Cods Roe"},{"content":"Place cods roe, lemon juice and garlic in mixing bowl then blend <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Place a jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in rapeseed oil then set aside."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Mix <b>speed 3<b>, while slowly pouring rapeseed oil from jug onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades."},{"content":"Add hot water. Place jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in peanut oil. Mix <b>speed 3<b>, while slowly pouring peanut oil from jug onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades. Let mixture rest for 5 minutes then transfer to a piping bag fitted with a 1 cm plain nozzle. Chill in fridge for 30 minutes until needed. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Horseradish Cream"},{"content":"Place horseradish in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and pour boiling water over then leave to soak for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Place drained grated horseradish in mixing bowl. Add vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper then blend <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add cream and whip <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Whip again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a 0.5 cm nozzle then chill in fridge until needed."},{"content":"When éclairs are completely cool, pipe cods roe into them through slits. Pipe a line of horseradish cream on top then garnish with caviar and mustard cress before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["These are fun and fabulous, a bit of a blast from the past. However, with éclairs trending again I could not resist resurrecting this savoury beauty. Make small little éclairs for a canapé party or larger shapes for a finger buffet. You could splash out and use caviar if you wish."],"basicInfo":["advanced","30m","1h 55m","20 portions"]}